    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-04-12T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-04-12T18:00:00-05:00" n="876"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d876">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.6363 Manchuria/164: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-04-12T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 12, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>61. Your 77, April 10, 7 p.m., paragraph 4. British Ambassador on April 10 left
                    at Department a typed plain page<note n="86" xml:id="d876fn86">Not
                        printed.</note> bearing no designation, date or signature, which reads in
                    part to the effect that the Anglo-Dutch oil companies have suggested that the
                    California companies, if given a hint by the American Government, would be
                    prepared to unite with the British companies in refusing to provide crude oil
                    supplies for the refinery of the Manchuria Oil Company.</p>
                <p>Department notes apparent discrepancy between foregoing statement and report
                    given in your 77, April 10, 7 p.m., paragraph 4, which refers to supplies of
                    crude oil “to Japan.”</p>
                <p>British Embassy requests expression of Department’s views on whole subject.
                    Department is considering.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
